This paper discusses techniques for improving the quality of spreadsheets, which are commonly used in software engineering (cs.SE) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of Poka-Yoke, a concept from manufacturing, suggests a focus on process improvement and error prevention, which could also be relevant to programming languages (cs.PL) and cybersecurity (cs.CY). Additionally, the paper's emphasis on spreadsheet layout and structure could be applicable to computer-aided design (cs.CE).
